question: 番号札
sourceMnemonic: You know <ja>番号</ja> means "number" so add a <kanji>tag</kanji> to it and you have a <vocabulary>numbered tag</vocabulary>.
sourceReadingMnemonic: This is a jukugo word (<ja>番号</ja>) with a single-word kanji added. That means you have two on'yomi readings from the jukugo word and the kun'yomi reading from the single kanji (<ja>ふだ</ja>). Put them all together and you have the reading of this kanji!
